The good state has all four elements: contextual icon, helpful title, brief body, and direct CTA. The tone is friendly and action-oriented.

## Zero-Result Pattern

<Preview>
  <div class="p-6 bg-white font-sans max-w-sm border border-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
    <div class="text-center space-y-3">
      <div class="w-12 h-12 mx-auto bg-gray-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-2xl">
        🔍
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800">No results for "unicorn"</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Try a different search term, or browse all categories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-2 justify-center">
        <button class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 bg-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-200 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition-colors">Clear search</button>
        <button class="text-xs font-medium text-blue-600 bg-blue-50 hover:bg-blue-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition-colors">Browse all</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Preview>

## Quick Recap

- Empty states have three jobs: explain, direct, encourage.
- Two types: first-time (onboarding) and zero-result (recovery).
- Four components: icon, title, body, CTA. All are required.
- Never just text. Never blame the user.
